docs.abstract: At a debate for Virginia governor, Mr. Fairfax, the state’s lieutenant governor, denounced Mr. McAuliffe for urging him to resign after women accused Mr. Fairfax of sexual assault in 2019.
docs.snippet: At a debate for Virginia governor, Mr. Fairfax, the state’s lieutenant governor, denounced Mr. McAuliffe for urging him to resign after women accused Mr. Fairfax of sexual assault in 2019.
docs.lead_paragraph: Terry McAuliffe, the leading candidate in this year’s Democratic primary for Virginia governor, faced a flurry of attacks from his rivals at a debate on Tuesday night as they aimed to diminish his broad support from Black voters. In the most extraordinary broadside, the state’s Black lieutenant governor, Justin Fairfax, accused Mr. McAuliffe of treating him like George Floyd or Emmett Till after Mr. Fairfax was accused of sexual assault by two women in 2019.

headline.main: Justin Fairfax Accuses Terry McAuliffe of Treating Him Like Emmett Till
headline.print_headline: Rivals Launch Sharp Attacks On McAuliffe In Virginia

docs.abstract: The witnesses who testified this week are still tormented by that day.
docs.snippet: The witnesses who testified this week are still tormented by that day.
docs.lead_paragraph: It has been more than 10 months since George Floyd was pinned to the Minneapolis pavement, a knee hard on his neck as the life drained senselessly out of him and he moaned, again and again, “I can’t breathe.” The small group of people who were there — along with countless others who watched the horrifying video — have had all that time to come to terms with it, or at least to try.

headline.main: Listening to Those Who Saw George Floyd Die

docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — They met one evening four summers ago, and she was instantly drawn to his “great, deep, Southern voice.” She gave him her phone number that night, and they became close, exploring the city’s sculpture garden and its vibrant restaurant scene. Soon she was simply calling him “Floyd,” just like his friends did.

docs.abstract: As the Derek Chauvin trial heads to the jury, a look at attempts to improve policing.
docs.snippet: As the Derek Chauvin trial heads to the jury, a look at attempts to improve policing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since George Floyd’s death last May, dozens of states and local governments have changed their laws about police behavior. And yet police officers continue to kill about three Americans each day on average, nearly identical to the rate of police killings for as long as statistics exist.

docs.abstract: Times photographers captured the events across Minneapolis as the trial over the death of George Floyd began.
docs.snippet: Times photographers captured the events across Minneapolis as the trial over the death of George Floyd began.
docs.lead_paragraph: Minneapolis was a city of protest and remembrance during the first days of the trial of Derek Chauvin, the white former police officer who is on trial in the death of George Floyd, the Black man whose neck he knelt on for more than nine minutes during an arrest last May.

headline.main: On the Scene: Week 1 of the Trial of Derek Chauvin
headline.print_headline: Scenes From a City Holding Its Breath, Waiting for Justice

docs.lead_paragraph: The colorful mural, adorned with hearts, a portrait of a local activist and the words “Black Lives Matter,” stands out at a busy intersection in West St. Paul, a community nestled against the Twin Cities. It is a cherished symbol for many Black residents, a site of reflection and pride.
